Aaron Fernando:

"Though there are other decentralized marketplaces that use blockchain technology, [[Open Bazaar]] was the [https://www.openbazaar.org/ first of its kind] and is still going strong. Users are able to pay for goods in over fifty cryptocurrencies. Since there is no company or entity running it, there are no fees or limits to what can be bought or sold. Though significant technical differences exist, for the casual user, up-and-coming challengers such as Swarm City, Public Market, and Blockmarket will offer similar services with different features."
(https://www.shareable.net/blog/10-blockchain-projects-to-keep-an-eye-on)

